class Solution {
    public int longestSubsequence(String s, int k) {
        int countZero = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '0') countZero++;
        }
        int n = s.length();
        long val = k;
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++) {
            if ((val & (1L << i)) != 0) {
                count = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        if (count >= n) return countZero + n;
        int ans = countZero + count;
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0 && count >= 0; i--) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '1') {
                count--;
                ans++;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string to count zeros and then determines the number of bits required to represent k. It then checks the string from right to left, including '1's until the count of bits is exhausted, effectively forming the longest subsequence that represents a number less than or equal to k.
